 :tx/rationale "INV-REFLEXIVE-006 FORMALIZATION: Second-Order Epistemic Closure. STATEMENT: The system MUST apply its own coherence machinery (concept clustering, agreement detection, link extraction, convergence scoring, stagnation detection) to its own observation layer using the SAME functions it applies to domain observations. The result MUST be surfaceable via a single CLI command (braid observe list, braid observe search, or braid seed) within one invocation, without reading external documents. FALSIFICATION: This invariant is violated if: (1) An agent with 10+ observations from 2+ distinct agents cannot retrieve the top 3 convergent findings via braid observe search or braid seed in a single command. (2) The functions used for second-order analysis (find_agreement_clusters, extract_observation_links, detect_stagnation) differ from or duplicate the functions used for first-order domain analysis. (3) braid observe list on a store with 50+ observations produces output that an agent cannot use to identify the dominant knowledge themes (verified by: grouped output contains concept names with member counts). (4) braid observe show on an observation with 3+ outgoing links fails to display the link targets. VERIFICATION: V:PROP (proptest for scoring monotonicity), V:TYPE (ObservationSummary struct constrains valid states), integration test (multi-agent store produces convergent findings in seed), E2E script (12-step validation). TRACES TO: SEED.md S6 (observation-projection duality), ADR-FOUNDATION-014 (convergence thesis), ADR-FOUNDATION-030 (free energy gradient / steering). STAGE: 1. CONFIDENCE: 0.95."
